  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Although often not specifically trained for medicine, LLMs are now being utilized for a broader range of tasks, including medical language translation, patient communication, privacy protection, and workflow enhancement.",
    "They are also being integrated into CDSS and automating processes like discharge planning, coding, and billing 6, 27, 28.",
    "Despite their potential, issues such as the propagation of race-based medicine by LLMs have not yet been addressed in EHR implementations 27.",
    "However, several EHR vendors are moving forward with integrating generative AI across their platforms 29.",
    "For example, Epic announced plans to roll out more than 100 generative AI projects such as auto-adverse drug reaction tagging, patient-friendly report summaries, a hospital billing coding assistant and an \"explain my bill\" AI agent at the 2024 HIMSS conference 30."
  ],
